<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-939-102  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 939 102.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Dec 4 1989 n277 p12(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Telco refunds to come. (as result of FCC ruling)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A ruling by the Federal Communications Commission will result inthe refund of $75 million to users of high-capacity digitalservices.andP;  In its ruling, the FCC concluded an investigation offour year's duration concerning the strategic pricing ofhigh-capacity digital services in tariffs in effect between Oct 1,1985 and Dec 31, 1988.andP;  Strategic pricing, the practice ofcharging for a service based on factors other than cost, is areflection of telephone company concerns about the bypassing oftheir switched networks.andP;  The International CommunicationsAssociation (ICA) brought the action to the FCC, contending thatonly cost-based pricing was justified.andP;  Manufacturers, who dependon a stable, cost-based environment to sell their PBXs andmultiplexers, endorsed the ruling.andP;  FCC guidelines say that asingle high-capacity circuit should equal the price of four toeight voice grade circuits.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionBell Regional Holding CompaniesGovernment RegulationPricing PolicyTariffDigital CommunicationsTelephone CompaniesInternational Communications Association.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>